-- UniCredit sells to US asset manager risk on 910 mln euro loan portfolio 
-- By Danilo Masoni
-- Tue Jan 21, 2014 02:48AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Jan 21 (Reuters) - UniCredit <CRDI.MI> has sold to Mariner Investment Group junior and mezzanine risk on a 910 million euro ($1.23 billion)portfolio of Italian project finance loans, it said on Tuesday.

In a statement, Italy's biggest bank by assets said the deal with the U.S. asset manager frees up capital it will deploy into new business growth.